Four years ago, I started this beautiful art journey. My life has changed completely for the better because I found my purpose on this earth. I have always loved art as a kid and wanted to paint every day, and I can’t believe it’s finally come true. ❤️ 

As a kid growing up I was very shy, introverted and had a lot of anxiety, so I always felt different from others. The only things I looked forward to in school were art and gym class, especially when we got to play ball hockey. 🏒 

In the last 5-10 years leading up to my rediscovery of art, I knew something was missing in my life and something wasn’t right with my mental state. I felt like I was lost and my purpose was still unknown in this world. 

The day that changed my life forever was a conversation with a friend. 
He said, “What would you do if money didn’t matter to you?”
I said, “I guess I would probably live in a small cabin by the lake and paint every day.” I’ll probably do that when I’m retired in the next 20-30 years.“ 
He said “But Mike, you could be dead next week, next year so why wait.“  😮 

That quote was so powerful and changed my life forever. I went out to buy paint supplies and started learning to paint again. 

The memory of me as a 12-year-old kid painting for my favourite art teacher instantly came back to me. I used to love sharing all of my new art with him and the rest of the class. I'm now able to share my paintings with all of you now!

Over the last 4 years, it’s been a wonderful journey with lots of emotions, good and bad. Lots of drama, but I know the journey is never a straight line. I had to overcome lots of stressful situations. Negative messages, haters. But the many true followers who are so nice make up for it all. Whenever I’m feeling depressed I would go back and read some of your nice messages and reviews and it would make me feel happy again. 

All of you keep me motivated and I'm excited to share new paintings with all of you this year. 

Thank you from the bottom of my heart for all your love and support. 🙏☺️
Mike 

#artjourney 
#passion #lovehockey #loveart

“A violinist played for 45 minutes in the New York subway. A handful of people stopped, a couple clapped, and the violinist raised about $30 in tips.

No one knew this, but the violinist was Joshua Bell, one of the best musicians in the world. In that subway, Joshua played one of the most intricate pieces ever written with a violin worth 3.5 million dollars. And two days before he played in the subway, with again not many people appreciating his skills .

Joshua Bell sold out a Boston theatre, and the seats averaged about $100. 

The experiment proved that the extraordinary in an ordinary environment does not shine and is so often overlooked and undervalued.

There are brilliantly talented people everywhere who aren’t receiving the recognition and reward they deserve. But once they arm themselves with value and confidence and remove themselves from an environment that isn’t serving them, they thrive and grow.

Your gut is telling you something. Listen to it if it’s telling you where you are isn’t enough!

Go where you are appreciated and valued.”
💯 
———-

I’ve tried local indoor & outdoor art shows and people just walk by without glancing at my artwork. That gave me so much social anxiety. 

It’s all trial & error and a lesson for all the creatives out there! You just need to find your people! Maybe you’re looking in the wrong places and need to try something different!
Don’t give up on your passion! 🎨

Thanks to all of you for the love and support over the years. 🙏 🎨

Another artist added me on fb a couple years ago & today I found them advertising my art photoshopped as their own art. 😕
As an artist don’t they realise this is wrong? 🤔

This painting took me over 30 hours to paint and only took them 5 minutes to remove my name and add a different players name and called it their own. 

This is the 2nd artist that I’ve seen stealing my work and others selling my artwork on products. 
If anyone sees my work being used from anyone other than myself, please let me know & report it. 🚨 

Thanks so much 🙏

🎨 MikeNguyenArt.com

🔔 Big announcement! 🔔 
Today is my birthday 🎂& Mr. 🍪 is going to be a big brother in Feb 2024! 👨‍👩‍👦

Back in Jan 2019 my life changed forever when I rediscovered my passion for art. I had so much happy tears 🥹 crying, and reliving how much I loved painting. I finally felt like I had a purpose on this earth 🎨 

I’ve been painting what I love non stop for the last 4 years and that’s all I want to do from now on. It wouldn’t be the same without all of your love and support which means the world to me. I love getting the nice messages and comments from everyone! ❤️ 🙏 

When I found out the news i was going to be a father I had tears in my eyes. I’ve always dreamed of becoming a dad and having my own family but I knew I wasn’t emotionally or financially ready for it. The last couple of months my anxiety took over worrying about the health of my wife Tak & our child and that’s partially the reason I didn’t paint much this summer. I know my wife will be a wonderful mother. 

I know I want to give my kid the world and treat them with love and respect. Love them unconditionally and be their support all their life. I feel like it’s the perfect time to have a family after I found art.

To all the parents out there please send me some parenting tips. I can’t wait to share my passion for art and hockey with my baby. 
I want them to do whatever makes them happy… but my kid will be future NHL or PWHL star or maybe a famous musician or artist 😝

My life will change forever with less time for my passion as my focus now is to be here to support my wife, make sure she & the baby is healthy & happy & i can’t wait to meet and welcome my kid to this world.

I’m so happy to be at this stage in my art career and truly grateful for all your support helping me build our little business. But my main reason for painting is because I just want to feel loved and it has always been that way since grade 7 with my favourite art teacher. He made me feel loved.
I want to thank everyone over the last 5 years  that have ordered my work, left comments and shared my work with other sports fans. Thank you for making me feel loved. I never expected this amount of love, support and I truly feel special. I also never expected my art to be in homes all over the world. I don’t usually like to post personal stuff because of my social anxiety & mainly only post my art, but I wouldn’t have been at this stage of life or met any of you without it. 

Here’s some info about me for my new followers: 

My name is Mike and I am a watercolour sports artist. 

1. I was born in Vietnam, but my family fled to Canada for a better life when I was a kid. I was unconscious during the trip and was close to being thrown into the ocean.
2. I started drawing around age 8, and some of my first drawings are of my favourite sports idols. 
3. I’ve always loved playing and watching hockey since I was a kid. 
4. I remember having social anxiety in school but art & sports were my therapy. 
5. My favourite artist growing up was and still is Vincent Van Gogh. I admired all his paintings especially the Cafe in Paris. 
6. When I’m not painting I enjoy playing roller hockey. 
7. I’m a dog lover and Mr. Cookie 🍪 is my best buddy. He’s always relaxing next to me while I paint. 
8. I moved to Winnipeg in 2012 for my wife’s career with the symphony. We live in Winnipeg & Toronto throughout the year. Tak playing the violin 🎻 on stage inspires me to paint live on stage too one day. 
9. I have many goals with my art journey especially releasing my own art book and having a private art show one day.
10. I had a full circle moment when I reconnected with my favourite grade 7 art teacher after not seeing him for over 20 years. I’ve always loved sharing my work with him and happy to do it again. 
11. I was confused with my life prior to 2019 & still struggled with mental health daily but I now wake up and have a purpose! Painting is my therapy & brings me joy

I would love to get to know all of you. 😊🙏
Please share some info about yourself and why you chose to follow my my Art. 💙💙
thanks for your continued support 🙏
Mike
